---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Why Dingo's Den exists and what kind of notes are published here."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl py-6 md:py-12">
    <div
      class="grid gap-8 border-b border-border/70 pb-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.15fr)_minmax(220px,0.85fr)] md:items-end"
    >
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1
          class="font-structure-title text-5xl leading-tight tracking-[-0.04em] md:text-6xl"
        >
          A small notebook for frontend work that should stay learnable.
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm leading-7 text-muted-foreground md:text-base">
        Dingo&apos;s Den is where implementation details, framework edge cases,
        and interface decisions get written down before they disappear.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-12 py-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_240px]">
      <div class="prose-editorial">
        <p>
          Most posts here begin as something annoying, subtle, or easy to
          forget: a state bug, a design decision, a component behavior that only
          makes sense after tracing it twice.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is not volume. The goal is to keep useful explanations close,
          practical, and readable enough to revisit when the same problem shows
          up again.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you like notes that are opinionated, concise, and grounded in real
          implementation details, you&apos;ll probably feel at home here.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="eyebrow">Topics</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-7 text-muted-foreground md:text-base">
            React, Vue, component architecture, interaction polish, and frontend
            system design.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="eyebrow">Format</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-7 text-muted-foreground md:text-base">
            Short essays, implementation notes, and examples that stay close to
            the code.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="eyebrow">Follow</p>
          <a href="/rss.xml" class="editorial-link">Subscribe via RSS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
